current_subtask:
  summary: Make first run feel like a normal consumer app: tap Instagram or Reddit and the native picker opens. The product must not expose “files,” “exports,” profiles, or storage as concepts.
  last_change: User rejected even the simplified two-step download/file wording. Main experience is now one app button per source; technical mechanics stay underneath.
  current_ci:
    - overlay validation: success on head 957e3f7
    - kernel parity: success on head 957e3f7
    - phone onboarding/import: success on head 957e3f7
    - Pages build: in progress on head 957e3f7
  final_product_changes:
    - remove name/handle from first run entirely
    - make each platform card a single IMPORT INSTAGRAM / IMPORT REDDIT action
    - open the native picker directly from that action
    - keep a tiny NEED YOUR DOWNLOAD? recovery link only for users who do not already have it
    - remove visible file/export/storage jargon
    - update real-touch tests and docs atomically
  done_when: A brand-new user sees a cool app, taps Reddit, chooses the Reddit download from the native system picker, and reaches a feed without learning Sideways architecture.

